Text of Introduce OpenMLDB: The OpenMLDB Feature Platform is a Feature Store service based on a feature database. Users use SQL to define features, select features to generate offline samples in offline scenarios, and choose features for real-time feature calculation in online scenarios.
Text of Insert Single Row: Users can directly insert single-row data into an online database based on the schema of the selected data table.
Text of Online Scenario: The online scenario is an online feature service that uses online data to provide a hard real-time online feature extraction interface. Users first create features, and then select features to deploy the feature service.
Text of Offline Scenario: Offline scenarios involve using distributed computing to perform feature computation on offline data and export sample files required for machine learning. Users first create features and then select these features to export offline samples.
Text of SQL Playground: Users can execute any OpenMLDB SQL statement. In online mode, it will request the online database, allowing for the addition, deletion, modification, and querying of online data; in offline mode, it will submit SQL for distributed execution, enabling offline exploration or sample generation.
Text of Computed Features: Users can precompute feature values and directly store them in the OpenMLDB online table, and then access the online table data for reading and writing features. If more complex feature computation logic is needed, it can be implemented through the command line or SDK by writing OpenMLDB SQL.
